summaries.short: Margene joins Bill at a convention; Nicki throws a party; Roman returns home; Rhonda resorts to blackmail.
summaries.full: Rebuffed by Barb, Bill asks Margene to accompany him to a Bar Owners' trade convention. Alby realizes that Juniper Creek has been robbed, and thinks he knows by whom. Nicki tries to orchestrate a celebration at Juniper Creek, but ends up moving it to her house when Alby objects.

summaries.short: Bill attempts to barter with Alby; Barb reaches out to her mother; Pam makes Margene a proposition.
summaries.full: Liberated by his trip to the convention, Bill makes Alby a tempting offer in the wake of Nicki's disclosure about Weber Gaming. Barb learns that her mother Nancy is getting remarried, and decides to use the occasion to try to make peace with her estranged family. Scott tests the limits of his relationship with Sarah, precipitating a visit from Bill.

summaries.short: Margene finds herself wielding a swing vote; Rhonda stays in the spotlight; Lois reaches out to Bill.
summaries.full: Bill enlists Nicki to sell Barb and Margene on Weber Gaming, with predictable results. In the wake of the latest public blemish on Juniper Creek, Bill calls an emergency UEB meeting that Alby ends up crashing. Burned by Frank, a distraught Lois fights to get back into Bill's good graces, and turns to an unexpected source for advice.

summaries.short: In the Season Two finale, the Henricksons are rocked by an unexpected guest on the eve of Pioneer Week.
summaries.full: Season Two finale. Foiled by Alby in his attempt to gain UEB support, Bill resorts to a new tack to try to bring down his nemeses. Preparing for the festivities surrounding Salt Lake City's Pioneer Week parade, the Henricksons are rocked by the appearance of an unexpected guest.

summaries.short: Bill proposes a 'seventh day off' schedule to his wives, and cons Roman into retaliating against the Greenes.
summaries.full: Stressed out from the Weber deal and exhausted by Margene's sexual appetite, Bill proposes that he take a night off from the wives every seventh day. With the Weber deal still in doubt, Bill continues to play both sides of the inter-compound dispute, hoping to incite Roman to take retaliatory measures that will finish off the Greenes.

summaries.short: In the Season Three premiere, Bill pitches a Mormon-friendly casino, with unexpected help from Margene.
summaries.full: In the Season Three premiere, Bill pitches a Mormon-friendly casino, with unexpected help from Margene. Meanwhile, an annual block party becomes the battleground for Bill to defend the family against neighborhood gossip, and for Nicki to defend her lifestyle as the daughter of Roman Grant.

summaries.short: Margene's mother visits the Henricksons; Roman's rivals force Bill to play a dangerous game.
summaries.full: Margene's dysfunctional past is illuminated when her mother Ginger pays a visit to the Henricksons. With tensions at a fever pitch as federal agents close in on the fugitive polygamist leader Orlean Abbot, Bill plays a dangerous end-game to land Weber Gaming, pitting Roman against the Greenes and vice-versa.
